text: Génesis Valentín Suárez (born 20 March 1998) is a Puerto Rican female badminton player. In 2013, she became the runner-up at the Carebaco International tournament in the women's doubles event. In 2014, she competed at the Central American and Caribbean Games in Veracruz, Mexico.
